FreetuxTV is a Linux media player based on GTK+ and LibVLC for watching 
and recording free WebTV, WebRadio and WebCam channels on a PC. It can 
also be used for importing, watching and recording TV channels from 
Tvheadend streaming server. It adds new groups of channels from M3U 
playlists, it imports and plays TV and Radio channels from Tvheadend,
it listens to WebRadio services, plays TV (Free, SFR and WebTV). It can
play in fullscreen mode or mini mode. It can record selected channels
including with timer recording. Supports keyboard multimedia keys.

This requires VLC.
